# Commit Message Rules

Always follow these rules (enforced by `commitlint.config.js`) when generating commit messages.

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

[optional body]

[optional footer]
```

## Types (only these are allowed)

`feat` | `fix` | `docs` | `style` | `refactor` | `perf` | `test` | `chore` | `ci` | `build` | `revert`

## Rules

- **type**: required, lowercase only
- **scope**: optional, lowercase or UPPERCASE, in parentheses
- **subject**: required, max 120 chars, no trailing `.`, no `StartCase`/`PascalCase`/`UPPER_CASE`
- **body**: optional — blank line before it, max 120 chars per line
- **footer**: optional — blank line before it, max 100 chars per line, use for `Closes #N`, `BREAKING CHANGE:`

## Examples

```
feat(auth): add email verification on signup
fix(api): handle null session on token refresh
refactor(supabase): extract auth helpers into shared module
chore(deps): update next to v15.3
ci: add lint check to GitHub Actions workflow
```

## Breaking change

```
feat(api)!: rename /v1/orders to /v1/checkout

BREAKING CHANGE: clients must migrate to /v1/checkout before 2026-07-01.
```
